          "email": "faaland1@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2015-07-09 19:15:29.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-6816 utils: remove libzfs_load_module() call",
        "message": "LU-6816 utils: remove libzfs_load_module() call\n\nRemove libzfs_load_module() call from the OSD.  The function is no\nlonger exported by libzfs2 in ZFS master, as it was intended as an\ninternal function to begin with.  libzfs_init(), which is already\nbeing used to set up the OSD, loads the module if necessary.\n\nThe intent of the call to libzfs_load_module apparently was to make\nzfs_init() fail silently at sites using ldiskfs, but fail with an error\nmessage if ZFS initialization failed where the ZFS backend was actually\nbeing used.  It's not clear that the code accomplished that anyway.\n\nHandling such error conditions will be dealt with in a separate ticket\nas it's a larger concern.\n\nSigned-off-by: Olaf Faaland <faaland1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: I6828e0aa8edbd318f5f5f820828d635ee060acb8\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
